            <term xml:id="term-k000110-6" xml:lang="en" type="literal_translation">tile ends (lit.)</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000110-1" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000110-1">barrel tile ends</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000110-7" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000110-2">eaves-tile ends</term>
            <note type="Note (brief)"> 
               <p xml:lang="en">Type of <term ref="/keyword/k000109">barrel tile (筒瓦 tongwa)</term> used to cap the end of a line of covering tiles at the eaves.</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant">瓦當的本意是瓦頭.現指 <term ref="/keyword/k000109">筒瓦</term> 的一種，剖面如 "┍—",作為蓋瓦用於檐頭以遮擋檐部.如<term ref="/keyword/k000051">明</term><term ref="/keyword/k000070">清</term>的 <term ref="/keyword/k000108">"勾頭"</term>.在清代文獻中，"瓦當"似通常專指<term ref="/keyword/k000069">秦</term><term ref="/keyword/k000030">漢</term>等較早時期的瓦當.</p>
            </note>
